<div class="row">
    <div class="col-md-6">
        <h2>Miles to Metric Converter</h2>
        <p>
            Ever wanted to know how many millimeters your drive to work was? Well, here is the place to figure it out.
            By clicking the button below you will be taken to a page where you can do just that. All you gotta do is 
            input the number of miles and the program will do the rest (I hope..).
        </p>
        <p><a class="btn btn-primary" @Html.ActionLink("Try it Out", "Converter", "Home")</a></p>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-6">
        <h2>Color Chooser</h2>
        <p>
            Ever wanted to know what two colors mixed together would look like? Well, here is the place to find out.
            By clicking the button you will be able to pick two colors and mix them. The only problem is you need to know 
            the Hexidecimal value of the colors (I would Google it, if you actually want to know what certain colors would 
            look like... otherwise just enjoy plugging in random things). After that the code will create a masterpiece with the colors 
            chosen. (By masterpiece I mean it will mix the two colors, that's all. No drawing.)
        </p>
        <p><a class="btn btn-primary" @Html.ActionLink("Check it Out", "Create", "Color")</a></p>
    </div>
</div>